<%# Docs chapter 03 — the signals. Finders vs nudges, then the twelve with
    blurb + detail from src/signals.js (the single source of truth shared
    with the home grid). Copy rule: simple words, no hyphens in visible text. %>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('../partials/head', { title: 'The signals — how it works' }) %>
</head>
<body class="min-h-screen bg-paper font-sans text-ink antialiased">
  <%- include('../partials/frame') %>
  <%- include('../partials/nav') %>

  <main class="relative mx-auto max-w-6xl overflow-hidden px-6 py-12">
    <span class="pointer-events-none absolute -right-10 top-6 select-none font-serif text-[15rem] font-extrabold leading-none text-ink/[0.04]" aria-hidden="true">信</span>

    <div class="reveal relative">
      <%- include('../partials/docs-header') %>

      <div class="mt-10 max-w-3xl space-y-5 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink/85">
        <p>
          One measurement is an opinion. Several independent measurements
          that agree are a recommendation. The engine never trusts a single
          signal, not even the story fingerprint, because every signal has
          a blind spot: summaries miss tone, tags miss plot, studios change
          staff, genres are coarse. Each signal sees one face of a show,
          and the system is the panel of them voting together.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="mt-12">
        <span class="font-serif text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">猟師と判事</span>
        <span class="jp-sub">ryoushi to hanji — finders and nudges</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="mt-5 max-w-3xl space-y-5 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink/85">
        <p>
          The eight live signals come in two kinds, and the difference is
          about how selective each one can afford to be.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Finders</strong> go hunting across the whole catalog. The
          story fingerprint, the tag match, the genre overlap and the
          studio signal each bring back their hundred best candidates.
          These four earn that job because they are picky: their hundredth
          best match still means something.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Nudges</strong> would make terrible hunters. Thousands of
          shows aired the same year, run the same length, share a format or
          a source, so "same year" points everywhere and nowhere. Instead
          of hunting, era, episode count, source material and format score
          the candidates the finders already brought back, and push each
          one up or down the ranking. A candidate found by story and tags
          that also matches the era and the length rises; one that matches
          nothing else settles lower.
        </p>
        <p>
          On the cards you see, the named signals are the finders that
          brought the show in. The nudges work in silence, because "found
          by" and "adjusted by" are different claims and the label answers
          the first one.
        </p>
      </div>

      <%# ——— The twelve, with honest status ——— %>
      <h2 class="mt-14">
        <span class="font-serif text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">十二の信号</span>
        <span class="jp-sub">juuni no shingou — the twelve signals</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink/85">
        Eight signals vote today and a ninth stands guard at the checkpoint.
        The remaining three are listed with honest status labels, because a
        roadmap you can see beats a feature that quietly does not exist.
      </p>

      <ol class="mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 gap-px border border-ink/15 bg-ink/15 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <% signals.forEach((s, i) => { %>
        <li class="bg-paper p-5">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-3">
            <p class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
              <span class="font-serif text-lg font-extrabold text-ink/30"><%= String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0') %></span>
              <span class="meta"><%= s.name %> <span class="text-ink/40">— <%= s.kanji %></span></span>
            </p>
            <% if (s.status === 'live') { %>
            <span class="meta shrink-0 bg-sakura px-1.5 py-0.5 text-paper">live</span>
            <% } else if (s.status === 'ready') { %>
            <span class="meta shrink-0 border border-ink/50 px-1.5 py-0.5">ready</span>
            <% } else { %>
            <span class="meta shrink-0 text-ink/40"><%= s.status %></span>
            <% } %>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm font-medium leading-relaxed text-ink/80"><%= s.blurb %></p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink/60"><%= s.detail %></p>
        </li>
        <% }) %>
      </ol>

      <%- include('../partials/docs-pager') %>
    </div>
  </main>

  <%- include('../partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
